I ordered a bereavement bouquet for a friend in Palm Desert through palmspringsflorist.net. I was able to add a hand-written card for a small charge, which was a nice touch given the sad occasion. They were delivered within a few hours, and Jordan sent an email confirming their delivery. It could not have been an easier process.

Palm Springs Florist is a little more expensive than others in the area. But their designs are so much more unique than those cookie-cutter catalog offerings, and the vessels they use are more suitable for modern aesthetics. I also enjoyed the personalized service of a local business with an established history.  Highly recommended to anyone who needs to send beautiful flowers in the Palm Springs area.</Text>

<gmap_id>0x808f7e26b45d66ff:0x50d63494858ed30e< /gmap_id><Rating>5< /Rating>< text>
Mazra had us at hello when we try out their family pack  to end 2020 at home during this pandemic.

This is an impressive spread of high quality Mediterranean food that is worth the value. Their website with online ordering interface is also much better in terms of allowing the restaurant to keep their already razor thin profit margin during this difficult time of the pandemic. Our curbside pick-up experience was also seamless, with friendly and prompt service from their lovely staff.

We ordered the deluxe charcoal kebab family pack which included a spread of their perfectly seasoned and charcoal grilled chicken, kofta, beef, and lamb chop, which came with a family size tray of basmati rice, freshly baked pitas, and two sides. We opted for their fresh hummus and cucumber yogurt (Tzatziki).

We were especially impressed at how fresh and the detailed care Mazra takes to wrap our takeout orders. The presentation is beyond expectation, I mean, just look at my accompanying pictures, they're so pleasing to look at. This type of attention to detail is hard to miss and it conveys that Mazra is one of those rare fast-casual places that is actually of a higher caliber than other fast-cash places.

Not only does Mazra exceeds in expectation for the care they take to pack and wrap our orders, the quality of their food is also exceptional. If you pay attention to the picture of the kebob tray, you will notice that they line the tray with Lavash. Our whole rotisserie chicken was also carefully wrapped in Lavash which probably helps with keeping the bird moist during transit.  All of the kebab was fresh tasting, tender, and moist. I often shy away from lamb dishes because they tend to be very gamy due to improper handling, but Mazra's lamb chop was perfect; it was well-cooked and tender.

Their hummus was creamy and the little gems of pomegranate sprinkled over its top pays a perfect sweet-tangly complement to its overall profile.  Their Tzatziki is perfectly tangy and fresh-tasting that one simply may have a hard time stopping oneself at second or third helpings-good thing it is also a healthy option.

I haven't been so starry-eyed impressed with getting take out like I have with this experience with Mazra. I really wish them future prosperity and hope that they maintain this consistency of high quality food and perfect pricing for the value. Their attention to detail does not go unnoticed and I am so ecstatic to have found a place like Mazra.  Happy New Year's Eve and good riddance 2020. Mazra is a perfect way to celebrate the end of this trying year.< /text>

< review>
I've been doing business with them since around 2005, and every single call, every single transaction, and the core team has been very helpful, explains things adequately, and does everything to follow-up on their promises.  I've purchase two high-end spas from them, and one high-end stove/insert - I'm in the process of receiving/installing the 2nd spa from them, after replacing the previous one (purchase from them) that lasted just fine ~13 years.  The stove/insert not only keeps our entire uninsulated 1904 build colonial revival two story home *very* warm, but it has had *only* maintenance done on it since we purchased from them around ~10 years ago.  I think these folks are definitely a "safe bet" for these products - they know what they're doing!< /review>

<user_id>113924212336476780809< /user_id>< resp>

< review>
You can't get a better place to buy hot tubs and gas inserts. Our experience with Dan and Nick has been nothing less than excellent. From the time we first bought our hot tub, to our purchase and installation of our gas insert was quite good. With our hot tub, Nick who we first met and bought our tub from, was outstanding in his approach and ways of teaching you how the different tubs functioned.

We have to give kudos also for the two outfits they use to deliver and install our tub and insert. Dominic (I think that was his name) delivered and gently put down our tub and made sure it was was exactly where we wanted it and showed me the different parts. He did not install the electrical outlet, etc., but he was good at laying the tub down, so gently.

Whenever I have needed help with figuring out the chemicals needed, and questions about the tub, Nick was my primary go-to person. He has been a good contact, and when I needed to talk he was there.

Four months later, we went back to inquire about gas inserts, and of course, we purchased one. Now this is where our happiness went a few pegs down. We bought our insert in December, and it turns out that is not a good time to buy gas inserts. It shipped from and was made in Canada (go Canucks!). Canadiens it turns out, like to run off on vacation in December. We were hoping for a install before the holidays. Instead it finally came just after the new year.

We had a contractor, "Moises" (sorry the name of the company is just not coming up), recommended by Berkeley Heat Tubmakers, his crew did an amazing job on the insert in less than eight hours. And our gas insert works amazingly well.

You won't go wrong with this group of people. They are very good at their jobs.<//review>

I am a big sucker for scones so I really liked the freshness and lightness of this lemon blueberry scone! Definitely a contrast to the more crumbly golden-crust scones out there, but a true delight especially with their solid decaf! I appreciate that because a lot of places neglect their decaf offerings. The coconut macaroon was light and fluffy much like a meringue. Plenty of seating with proper distancing on the patio. Attentive service, too! Wonderful in every regard.< /Review>

< Review>
I know they focus on gluten free cupcakes, but I've only had their other pastries. They're super tasty for the most part, and I've never been more impressed with the quality of ingredients in a pastry - fresh blueberries, fresh lemon zest, high quality cheddar, etc. The scones are a little chewy but delicious. The muffins are, in my opinion, their best item. I'm not even a blueberry muffin person but I've never had a better one. Strangely enough, I haven't found their meals to be as good as their pastries. It seems like someone is a very good gluten free pastry chef but not as good of a general chef - the avocado toast with tomatoes had great toast but average avocado and tomatoes.<//Review>

<Pictures>None</Pictures><user_name>William Schiewe<//user_name>< Rate>
5<//Rate>
< userid>
108965144562673792991< /userid>
< text>
A True American Gun Shop

If you want an accurate measure of a modern gun store, visit when everyone is angry over lockdowns AND buying guns. As long as Valley Gun remains on the frontlines of the 2nd Amendment, they'll continue to receive my business over other local stores.

You can't blame crowds or ammo shortages on shops these days. It's a sign of the times, but fortunately, Valley Gun doesn't gouge on price. I understand the phrase "out of stock" better than $50 for a box of 9mm.

Their gunsmiths are experienced too, versus other stores that would rather sell you a new firearm instead. They've serviced WWII surplus, Glocks, AR-15s, and even delicate .22 rimfires that cost more to repair than replace. Valley Gun is happy to let you pay extra for those family heirlooms because sometimes, it's worth the additional cost.

Of course, these are all secondhand reports I've heard from others. I lost all my firearms in a boating accident. If I ever find them, I'll be sure to update this review with how effective their gunsmiths are at fixing water damage.

Jokes aside, part of what makes this shop (and staff) special is the variety. Their storefront isn't merely hunting supplies, 'boomer fudds,' or concealed carry holsters. You can find collectible guns, reloading supplies, optics, storage safes, and even an ample selection of spare magazines.

So what's the downside? They don't sell MRE's or Hawaiian T-shirts. That's about it.  Go visit Valley Gun today before our corporate-slash-government overlords drive them out of business permanently.< /text>

0x80ea6993b43773f7:0x74de28025556e706</Gmap_id>

Stuart Lancaster (Stubaroo)</name>

0x80ea6993b43773f7:0x74de28025556e706< /gmap_id>
<Text>Valley gun is so slammed with people not knowing what they should buy. The staff is over whelmed and is always doing paperwork at the counter. Of you just need something small that doesn't require a background check be ready to wait. The cases for handgun are almost all empty so know what you want before hand and get on the waiting list. <Rating>5</Rating>< Review>
Came here for a youth baseball tournament. The facilities are amazing, clean, modern, and the BEST part is the food. I know it's wierd that I'm saying that but this is not your typical snack bar. It's a food truck with some delicious food offerings - nachos that a grown man can't even finish, bacon burgers, club sandwiches, fries! Can't wait for our next tournament.</Review>

< Text>
This is a very nice place in the middle of no where, just off I-5, easy off and on. Several places to eat, all fast food, all are walking distance away.
Hotel is perfect, very reasonable priced. Clean room, comfortable bed, nice hot shower, all the amenities you would expect.
Pleasantly surprised by the young lady that checked me in, her name was Felicia. What a plus she was, went beyond what you would expect, very helpful, explaining everything, please tell her thank you for her help.</Text>

<Date>1617246416192<//Date><text>I came into town as an early frost was making it too cold to ride. I didn't have high expectations because it's just a tiny town and a little Best Western.  But it might be the most pleasant Best Western experience I've ever had. Felicia at front desk was absolutely brilliant and instead of asking for all kinds frivolous things like license plate numbers and other such red tape, recognised the needs of a weary traveller and had my room ready and had me checked in record time. Literally as soon as the Room was booked online, the key was available to me. The rooms are spacious, clean and very comfortable. It was a Saturdy night and the hotel was rather full, but it was quiet, peaceful and I slept great. I woke up refreshed and ready for the rest of my trip. The breakfast was just a grab n go deal so familiar to post Covid-19 travelers.  I rarely review properties I stay at but this exceptional property deserves an exception.
If your riding a motorcycle down I5 and dusk is approaching and you're within 25 miles of Firebaugh, my advice to you, brother (or sister) is to check out the Best Western.  They even went so far as to suggest a place for me to park my motorcycle so it was both covered and watched during the night . Which I thought was next level above and beyond.
Although there's not much to do in Firebaugh, California from my humble point of view.  I would consider vacationing there just to delight in relaxing  at the Best Western apricot inn. Every Best Western should have a "Felicia" at the front desk. Life would be much less taxing.

Tugboat-< /text></record>

Great value hotel stay. Good, clean room, proper bath/ shower setup with a separate vanity sink area. Newer furnishings and nice flat screen TV. Wifi included. Check-in was fast and personable. Room includes a microwave, fridge and room safe.  I understand there is also a pool, but I didn't take advantage of that particular amenity.

<Rating>2<//Rating>< text>
Staff was friendly (+ 1 star), and the breakfast was good (+1 star). The surrounding area is to be desired. I stayed in a ground level room facing the front parking lot.

What initially caught my attention was that the doorjam to my room looked like the door had previously been kicked in and the jam was glued back together as a repair (-1 star). Doors don't get kicked in for any old reason so seeing that gave me an uneasy feeling right off the bat. The rest of the room appeared clean. The beds were hard and weren't very comfortable though (-1 star).

There was a lot of foot traffic coming and going to nearby rooms and small groups of people loitering outside throughout the night. I kept hearing cars pull up in front of my window, doors opening and closing, and then cars driving away (-1 star).

Overall it wasn't a very restful night. Probably won't be back.< /text>

The Best Western in Firebaugh, CA is a very nice stay.  They provide a very nice breakfast beginning at 5:00.  This is much appreciated by me as I am on the road early, so I can take advantage of breakfast.  Most places are later than 5:00 am.

< text>
I came upon this hotel by accident and was surprised to find it almost completely booked. Now I see why; every member of the staff are friendly and professional and go the extra mile to make me feel at home. The amenities are also great for a hotel of this size; high-speed internet and, (when the lobby is not under renovation as it is currently), a hot breakfast. The laundry machines come in handy too. Everything works! I never have a problem with the fridge, microwave, ice machine or TV as I have experienced at some other hotels. They are quick to give me an extra blanket or anything I need during my stays.
I love the staff and would never stay anywhere else on highway 5.</text>

3</Rate>
< review>
A decent property with clean, good-sized rooms and a nice pool.  In spite of the proximity to I-5 room noise didn't seem to be a problem.  The ceilings are a little thin, so if you're a light sleeper, try the second floor.  And with the restaurant closed, they attempt to bridge that gap with an included breakfast.  So it's a comfortable place if you want to stop when nothing's around.

Two issues.
- Staff isn't terribly service oriented. We were there with a large group that filled up quite a bit of the motel (not the typical travelers who might try to be on the road at 6 am) and they couldn't be bothered with a request for help with some breakfast items slightly outside of their set hours.  One staff member ignored me and seemed more interested in having her own breakfast; another cited policy and refused to help. Strike one
- Be forewarned: a bigger issue is that several people in the same group had their credit card numbers stolen. Initially we assumed it was overseas hackers, but the Fresno County detectives are investigating it and haven't ruled out an inside job.  I hate to post this and scare people away from a decent place to sleep, but also want to forewarn people stopping in.  I'll post again if we get an update.< /review>

<Review>Very nice staff, a pool and a place to stop in the middle of nowhere! What's not to love?

Well I'll tell you- bugs. They have a sign at the front desk warning that as this is a dry, farming community, there are many different bugs that try to live in the hotel as well. I underestimated this warning.

At first, when I settled in, there was one fly. He kept buzzing around the room, and I couldn't catch him. Oh well, I thought, I can live with that.

Then I woke up in the middle of the night with no less than five spider bites. Eh, stuff happens like that sometimes.

But I couldn't fall asleep, because there was a gnat this time! (smaller than the fly, who was also still buzzing.)

Finally I got up to take a shower and saw a giant cockrouch/beetle if some sort in the shower. At this point I wasn't even fazed. "Eh, there's enough room for me next to him, and at least he won't bite."

All in all, nice hotel, great breakfast, kind and helpful staff, but extra, six legged guests will try and tag along.<//Review>< Resp>

If I wanted to get the lower rate, I‚Äôd have to book it myself on the website.  I asked her if she was serious.  Yep, totally.  So I spent 15 very painful minutes right there in front of her, making the reservation on my phone.  Non refundable.  Pecking in my credit card and all that.  Hit submit, get a reservation confirmation.  Here it is, she says.  And proceeds to ask me for my credit card number to pay for it.  Again.  My reservation I just made was non refundable.  At his point I figured what the heck, we just need to sleep, so I gave her the card anyway.  We‚Äôll see if I end up with double charge.
The room was fine.  Beds comfortable and clean (pillows were the lumpy foam kind  though).  The bathroom was a little unloved.
